Definition:
  for all v0, ((v0 is a successor ordinal) iff (v0 is an ordinal number and for some v1, (v1 is an ordinal number and v0 is equal to \ORDsucc( v1 ))))

Theorem:
  for all v0, (for all v1, (if v0 is an ordinal number and v1 is an ordinal number then (if \ORDsucc( v0 ) is equal to \ORDsucc( v1 ) then v0 is equal to v1)))
Proof:
  \ORDsucc( \alpha ) is equal to \ORDsucc( \beta )
  \alpha is a subclass of \beta
  Proof:
    \gamma is an element of \alpha
    \gamma is an element of \alpha \SETunion \SETsingleton{ \alpha } and \alpha \SETunion \SETsingleton{ \alpha } is equal to \ORDsucc( \alpha ) and \ORDsucc( \alpha ) is equal to \ORDsucc( \beta ) and \ORDsucc( \beta ) is equal to \beta \SETunion \SETsingleton{ \beta }
    \gamma is an element of \beta or \gamma is equal to \beta
    \gamma is equal to \beta
    \beta is an element of \alpha
    \beta is equal to \beta \SETunion \SETsingleton{ \beta } \SETdiff \SETsingleton{ \gamma } and \beta \SETunion \SETsingleton{ \beta } \SETdiff \SETsingleton{ \gamma } is equal to \alpha \SETunion \SETsingleton{ \alpha } \SETdiff \SETsingleton{ \gamma } and \alpha \SETunion \SETsingleton{ \alpha } \SETdiff \SETsingleton{ \gamma } is equal to \alpha \SETdiff \SETsingleton{ \gamma } \SETunion \SETsingleton{ \alpha }
    \alpha is an element of \beta
    \alpha is an element of \beta and \beta is an element of \alpha
    falsity holds
  Qed.
  \beta is a subclass of \alpha
  Proof:
    \gamma is an element of \beta
    \gamma is an element of \beta \SETunion \SETsingleton{ \beta } and \beta \SETunion \SETsingleton{ \beta } is equal to \ORDsucc( \beta ) and \ORDsucc( \beta ) is equal to \ORDsucc( \alpha ) and \ORDsucc( \alpha ) is equal to \alpha \SETunion \SETsingleton{ \alpha }
    \gamma is an element of \alpha or \gamma is equal to \alpha
    \gamma is equal to \alpha
    \alpha is an element of \beta
    \alpha is equal to \alpha \SETunion \SETsingleton{ \alpha } \SETdiff \SETsingleton{ \gamma } and \alpha \SETunion \SETsingleton{ \alpha } \SETdiff \SETsingleton{ \gamma } is equal to \beta \SETunion \SETsingleton{ \beta } \SETdiff \SETsingleton{ \gamma } and \beta \SETunion \SETsingleton{ \beta } \SETdiff \SETsingleton{ \gamma } is equal to \beta \SETdiff \SETsingleton{ \gamma } \SETunion \SETsingleton{ \beta }
    \beta is an element of \alpha
    \beta is an element of \alpha and \alpha is an element of \beta
    falsity holds
  Qed.
Qed.

